solution: ```class Solution {
    public int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0) {
            int consume = Math.min(mainTank, 5);
            distance += consume * 10;
            mainTank -= consume;
            if (consume == 5 && additionalTank > 0) {
                mainTank++;
                additionalTank--;
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(mainTank)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Simulate fuel consumption in 5-liter chunks; each time 5 liters are used and the auxiliary tank has fuel, transfer 1 liter. Loop ends when main tank is empty. Simple loop with constant-time operations.

